						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: ⎯⎯ Year: ⎯⎯</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged and the language is also faulty. It is engraved in peculiar characters of about the tenth century A.D. It mentions various mercantile bodies <hi rend="italic">tisai-āyiratt-</hi> <hi rend="italic">aiññūṟṟuvar, nānādēśi</hi> and <hi rend="italic">vīrasauravi</hi>, and seems to refer to the conversion of a village (Vākūr ?) to <hi rend="italic">vīrattāvaḷam.</hi> It also appears to fix duties on certain communities. The record also refers to the above mercantile commodities of Sakku-maṅgalam. Other details are not clear.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
